#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:442
msgid "Costs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:444
msgid ""
"The objective function of the model is to minimize the net present value "
"of the system's cost. This includes capital cost, fixed O&M cost, "
"variable cost and fuel cost by cost type, technology cost, transmission "
"line cost by the source of cost, and operation cost and planning cost by "
"the source of cost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:446
msgid "The cost equations are defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:-1
msgid "Calculation of system-wide total cost"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:453
msgid ""
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{tech}}^{\\rm{var}} &= "
"\\frac{\\sum_{h,m,y,z,\\rm{e}}C_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{tech-var}}\\times "
"\\rm{gen}_{h,m,y,z,\\rm{e}}}{\\omega} \\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{var}}\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{line}}^{\\rm{var}} &= "
"\\frac{\\sum_{h,m,y,z_s,z_o}C_{y,z}^{\\rm{line-var}}\\times "
"\\rm{export}_{h,m,y,z_s,z_o}}{\\omega} \\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{var}}\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}^{\\rm{fuel}} & = "
"\\frac{\\sum_{h,m,y,z,\\rm{e}}C_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{fuel}}\\times "
"\\rm{gen}_{h,m,y,z,\\rm{e}}}{\\omega} \\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{var}}\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{tech}}^{\\rm{fix}} &= "
"\\sum_{y,z,\\rm{e}}C_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{tech-fix}}\\times "
"\\rm{cap}_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{existing-tech}}\\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{fix}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{line}}^{\\rm{fix}} &= "
"\\sum_{y,z_s,z_o}C_{y,z_s,z_o}^{\\rm{line-fix}}\\times "
"\\rm{cap}_{y,z_s,z_o}^{\\rm{existing-line}}\\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{fix}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{tech}}^{\\rm{inv}} &=  "
"\\sum_{y,z,\\rm{e}}C_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{tech-inv}}\\times "
"\\rm{cap}_{y,z,\\rm{e}}^{\\rm{tech-inv}}\\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{inv}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"\\rm{cost}_{\\rm{line}}^{\\rm{inv}} &= "
"\\sum_{y,z_s,z_o}C_{y,z_s,z_o}^{\\rm{line-inv}}\\times "
"\\rm{cap}_{y,z_s,z_o}^{\\rm{line-inv}}\\times "
"\\rm{factor}_{y}^{\\rm{inv}} \\times 0.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:474
msgid "Factors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:476
msgid ""
"To account for the variable factor, fixed factor, and capital factor, we "
"need to convert all future costs to their net present value. This means "
"adjusting for the time value of money so that all costs are expressed in "
"terms of today's dollars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:478
msgid ""
"We also assume that variable cost and fixed cost for non-modelled years "
"are assumed to be equal to the cost of the last modelled year preceding "
"them. This allows for consistent comparison across different time periods"
" and technologies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:480
msgid "**Variable Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:-1
msgid "Calculation of variable costs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:487
#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:525
msgid "Given the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:489
msgid "Variable cost of modeled year: :math:`B`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:490
#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:528
msgid "Discount rate: :math:`r`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:491
#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:529
msgid ":math:`m`-th modeled year: :math:`m = y - y_\\text{min}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:492
msgid "Depreciation periods: :math:`n`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:494
#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:532
msgid "The total present value can be calculated as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:496
msgid ""
"\\text{total present value} &= \\frac{B}{(1+r)^m} + "
"\\frac{B}{(1+r)^{m+1}} + \\cdots + \\frac{B}{(1+r)^{(m+k-1)}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"&= B(1+r)^{(1-m)}\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-k}}{r}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:502
msgid "And we can calculate the variable factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:504
msgid ""
"\\text{factor}_{y}^\\text{var} &= (1+r)^{1-m_y}\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-k_y}}{r} "
"\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"m_{y} &= y - y_\\text{min} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"k_{y} &= y_\\text{periods}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:512
msgid "**Fixed Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:514
msgid "We can equate the fixed factor with the variable factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:516
msgid ""
"\\text{factor}_{y}^\\text{fix} = \\text{factor}_{y}^\\text{var}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:518
msgid "**Investment Factor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:-1
msgid "Calculation of investment costs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:527
msgid ""
"Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC, or otherwise known as the "
"interest rate): :math:`i`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:530
msgid "Length of :math:`m`-th planning periods: :math:`k`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:534
msgid ""
"\\text{total present value} &= \\frac{P}{(1+r)^m} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"&= \\frac{\\frac{A}{(1+i)} + \\frac{A}{(1+i)^2} + \\cdots + "
"\\frac{A}{(1+i)^n}}{(1+r)^m} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"&= A\\frac{1-(1+i)^{-n}}{i}\\times\\frac{1}{(1+r)^m}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:542
msgid ""
"From the above, we can solve for the annualized cost of depreciation "
"periods, :math:`A`, as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:544
msgid "A = P\\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:548
msgid "The capital recovery factor is then calculated as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:550
msgid "\\text{capital recovery factor} = \\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:554
msgid ""
"Let's focus on the time periods that fall within the modelled time "
"horizon (indicated in black colour). We can calculate the length of time "
"periods, :math:`k`, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:556
msgid "k = y_\\text{max} - y"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:560
msgid "Using :math:`k`, we can calculate the net present value as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:562
msgid ""
"\\text{net present value} = \\frac{\\frac{A}{(1+r)} + \\frac{A}{(1+r)^2} "
"+ \\cdots + \\frac{A}{(1+r)^{\\text{min}(n, k)}}}{(1+r)^m} = A \\times "
"\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-\\text{min}(n,k)}}{r(1+r)^m}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:567
msgid "And we can calculate the investment factor as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:569
msgid ""
"\\text{factor}_{y}^\\text{inv} = "
"\\frac{i}{1-(1+i)^{-n}}\\times\\frac{1-(1+r)^{-\\text{min}(n,k)}}{r(1+r)^m}"
" \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:575
msgid "Constraints"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:578
msgid "Retirement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:580
msgid ""
"The model computes the retirement of each technology and transmission "
"line with these considerations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:582
msgid ""
"The historical capacity of the technology and transmission line is based "
"on its capacity ratio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:583
msgid "Each planning and scheduling period is based on the existing capacity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:585
msgid ""
"The existing capacity for each year, in each zone, for each technology, "
"is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:587
msgid ""
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}=\\sum_{{\\rm{age}}=1}^{{{T}}_e-(y-y_{\\rm{start}})}{{\\rm{CAP}}}_{{\\rm{age}},z,e}^{\\rm{inittech}}+\\sum_{y_{\\rm{pre}}={\\max}(y_{\\rm{start}},"
" "
"y-{{T}}_e)}^{y}{{\\rm{cap}}_{y_{\\rm{pre}},z,e}^{\\rm{invtech}}}\\quad\\forall"
" y,z,e \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:592
msgid ""
"The existing capacity of the transmission lines for each year, from "
":math:`z_{\\rm{from}}` zone to :math:`z_{\\rm{to}}`-th zone, is as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:594
msgid ""
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{existingline}}=\\sum_{{\\rm{age}}=1}^{{T}_{\\rm{line}}-(y-y_{\\rm{start}})}{{\\rm{CAP}}}_{{\\rm{age}},z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{initline}}+\\sum_{y_{\\rm{pre}}={\\max}(y_{\\rm{start}},"
" "
"y-{{T}}_{\\rm{line}})}^{y}{{\\rm{cap}}_{y_{\\rm{pre}},z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{invline}}}\\quad\\forall"
" y,z_{\\rm{from}}\\neq z_{\\rm{to}}\\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:600
msgid "Carbon Emission"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:602
msgid ""
"The model computes the carbon emissions for each year, based on the sum "
"of carbon emissions from each zone, and from each technology as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:604
msgid ""
"{\\rm{carbon}}_y=\\sum_{e\\in\\mathcal{E}}\\sum_{z\\in\\mathcal{Z}}\\sum_{m\\in\\mathcal{M}}\\sum_{h\\in\\mathcal{H}}\\left({{\\rm{CARBON}}}_{y,z,e}\\times"
" {\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\right)\\quad\\forall y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:610
msgid ""
"The calculated carbon emission for each year lower than its upper bound, "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:612
msgid ""
"{\\rm{carbon}}_y\\le{\\overline{{\\rm{CARBON}}}}_y\\quad\\forall y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:618
msgid "Power Balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:620
msgid ""
"The model computes the power balance for each hour, in each time period, "
"for each year, and in each zone, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:622
msgid ""
"{{\\rm{DEMAND}}}_{h,m,y,z}\\times\\Delta h = \\sum_{z_{\\rm{from}}\\in "
"{\\mathcal{Z}}\\backslash{\\{z\\}}}{{\\rm{import}}_{h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}},z}}"
" - \\sum_{z_{\\rm{to}}\\in "
"{\\mathcal{Z}}\\backslash{\\{z\\}}}{{\\rm{export}}_{h,m,y,z,z_{\\rm{to}}}}\\\\"
"\n"
"\\\\\n"
"+ \\sum_{e\\in {\\mathcal{E}}}{{\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e}} - \\sum_{e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}}}{{\\rm{charge}}_{h,m,y,z,e}}\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:630
msgid "Transmission"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:632
msgid ""
"We simplify the transmission of electricity as a transportation model. "
"The model computes the transmission loss for each hour, in each time "
"period, for each year, from :math:`z_{\\rm{from}}` zone to "
":math:`z_{\\rm{to}}` zone, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:634
msgid ""
"{\\rm{import}}_{h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}={\\rm{export}}_{h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}\\times\\eta_{z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{trans}}\\quad\\forall"
" h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}}\\neq z_{\\rm{to}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:639
msgid ""
"This model assumes that the transmitted power of each transmission line "
"is only constrained by the transmission capacity between two zones as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:641
msgid ""
"{\\rm{import}}_{h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}&\\le "
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{existingline}}\\times\\Delta"
" h\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}}\\neq z_{\\rm{to}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"{\\rm{export}}_{h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}&\\le "
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z_{\\rm{from}},z_{\\rm{to}}}^{\\rm{existingline}}\\times\\Delta"
" h\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z_{\\rm{from}}\\neq z_{\\rm{to}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:649
msgid "Power Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:651
msgid ""
"The power output of storage and each dispatchable (exclude hydropower) "
"technology (:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) is limited by the existing"
" installed capacity (:math:`{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}`) "
"and minimum technical output, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:653
msgid ""
"{\\underline{{\\rm{POWER}}}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\times "
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\le{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\le"
" {\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}}\\ \\&\\ {\\mathcal{DISP}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:658
msgid ""
"Since hydropower processes are explicitly modelled at the plant level in "
"PREP-SHOT, total hydropower output in zone :math:`z` "
"(:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e={\\rm{hydro}}}`) is the sum of the "
"plant-level hydropower output "
"(:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{\\it{s,h,m,y}}^{\\rm{hydro}}`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:660
msgid ""
"{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e={\\rm{hydro}}}=\\sum_{s\\ "
"\\in{\\mathcal{SZ}}_z}{\\rm{power}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{hydro}}\\quad\\forall"
" h,m,y,z \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:665
msgid ""
"Here, calculation of :math:`{\\rm{power}}^{\\rm{hydro}}_{s,h,m,y}` is "
"obtained by external net water head simulation procedure. In addition, "
":math:`{\\rm{power}}^{\\rm{hydro}}_{s,h,m,y}` is bounded between the "
"guaranteed minimum output "
"(:math:`{\\underline{{\\rm{POWER}}}}_s^{\\rm{hydro}}`) and the nameplate "
"capacity (:math:`{{\\rm{CAP}}}_s^{\\rm{hydro}}`), as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:667
msgid ""
"{\\underline{{\\rm{POWER}}}}_s^{\\rm{hydro}}\\le{\\rm{power}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{hydro}}\\le{{\\rm{CAP}}}_s^{\\rm{hydro}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:672
msgid ""
"For VRE, their power output is constrained by the capacity factors as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:674
msgid ""
"{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\le{{\\rm{CF}}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\times{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall"
" h,m,y,z,e\\in {\\mathcal{NDISP}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:679
msgid ""
"Regardless of the technology type,  actual power generation "
"(:math:`{\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) in a corresponding period "
":math:`\\Delta h` can be calculated based on the power output "
"(:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) and the generation efficiency "
"(:math:`\\eta_{y,e}^{\\rm{out}}`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:681
msgid ""
"{\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e} = {\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}\\times\\Delta "
"h\\times\\eta_{y,e}^{\\rm{out}}\\quad \\forall h,m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{E}}\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:686
msgid ""
"Note that :math:`\\eta_{y,e}^{\\rm{out}}=1` when :math:`e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{E}}\\backslash {\\mathcal{STOR}}`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:689
msgid "Power output variation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:691
msgid ""
"All technologies apart from non-dispatchable technology are limited by "
"the so-called ramping capability, meaning that the variation of their "
"power output in two successive periods is limited.  We introduce two non-"
"negative auxiliary variables: increment "
"(:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{up}}`) and decrement "
"(:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{down}}`) to describe changes in "
"power output in two successive periods (from :math:`h`-1 to :math:`h`) as"
" follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:693
msgid ""
"{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{up}}-{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{down}}={\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}-{\\rm{power}}_{h-1,m,y,z,e}\\quad\\forall"
" h,m,y,z,e\\ \\in {\\mathcal{E}}\\backslash {\\mathcal{NDISP}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:698
msgid ""
"When the power plant ramps up from :math:`h`-1 to :math:`h`, the minimum "
"of :math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{up}}` is obtained when "
":math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{down}}` becomes zero. Similarly, "
"when the power plant ramps down from :math:`h`-1 to :math:`h`, the "
"minimum of :math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{down}}` is obtained "
"when :math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{up}}` becomes zero. "
"Therefore, we can constrain the maximum ramping up and down respectively,"
" as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:700
msgid ""
"{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{up}}&\\le{{R}}_e^{\\rm{up}}\\times\\Delta"
" h\\times {\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall "
"h,m,y,z,e\\in {\\mathcal{E}}\\backslash {\\mathcal{NDISP}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:705
msgid ""
"{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{down}}&\\le{{R}}_e^{\\rm{down}}\\times\\Delta"
" h\\times {\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall "
"h,m,y,z,e\\in {\\mathcal{E}}\\backslash {\\mathcal{NDISP}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:710
msgid ""
"where :math:`{{R}}_e^{\\rm{up}}$/${{R}}_e^{\\rm{down}}` is the allowed "
"maximum/minimum ramping up/down capacity of technology :math:`e` in two "
"successive periods, expressed as a percentage of the existing capacity of"
" storage technology :math:`e`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:713
msgid "Energy storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:715
msgid ""
"Similar to the power discharging process, the charging power of storage "
"technology :math:`e` (:math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{{c}}`) is also "
"limited by the existing installed capacity and technical minimum charging"
" power (:math:`{\\underline{{\\rm{POWER}}}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{{c}}`) as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:717
msgid ""
"{\\underline{{\\rm{POWER}}}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{{c}}\\times "
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\le{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{{c}}\\le"
" {\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:722
msgid ""
"The charging generation (:math:`{\\rm{charge}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) and "
":math:`{\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{c}` need to meet the following formula:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:724
msgid ""
"{\\rm{charge}}_{h,m,y,z,e}={\\rm{power}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{c}}\\times\\Delta"
" h{\\times\\eta}_{y,e}^{{\\rm{in}}}\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:729
msgid ""
"Changes in stored electricity "
"(:math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}`)\\  in two successive"
" periods should be balanced by the charging "
"(:math:`{\\rm{charge}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) and discharging "
"(:math:`{\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e}`) processes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:731
msgid ""
"{\\rm{storage}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}-\\ "
"{\\rm{storage}}_{h-1,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}={\\rm{charge}}_{h,m,y,z,e}-{\\rm{gen}}_{h,m,y,z,e}"
" \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:736
msgid ""
"In addition, the initial (when :math:`h=h_{\\rm{start}}`) stored "
"electricity  "
"(:math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{h=h_{\\rm{start}},m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}`) of "
"storage technology :math:`e` in each month of each year can be calculated"
" based on the proportion of the maximum storage capacity, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:738
msgid ""
"{\\rm{storage}}_{h=h_{\\rm{start}},m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}={{\\rm{STORAGE}}}_{m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}\\times{{\\rm{EP}}}_e\\times"
" {\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:743
msgid ""
"The instantaneous storage energy level "
"(:math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}`) of storage "
"technology :math:`e` should not exceed the maximum energy storage "
"capacity, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:745
msgid ""
"{\\rm{storage}}_{h,m,y,z,e}^{\\rm{energy}}\\le{{\\rm{EP}}}_e\\times "
"{\\rm{cap}}_{y,z,e}^{\\rm{existingtech}}\\quad\\forall h,m,y,z,e\\in "
"{\\mathcal{STOR}} \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:751
msgid "Water balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:753
msgid ""
"Similar to the storage technologies, changes in reservoir storage "
"(:math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}`) in two successive "
"periods should be balanced by total inflow "
"(:math:`{\\rm{inflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}`) and total outflow "
"(:math:`{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:755
msgid ""
"{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}-{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h-1,m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}=\\Delta"
" "
"h\\times3600\\times\\left({\\rm{inflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}-{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}\\right)\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:760
msgid ""
"Here :math:`{\\rm{inflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}` consists of two "
"parts: the total outflow received from all immediate upstream reservoirs "
"(:math:`\\sum_{{\\rm{su}}\\in "
"{\\mathcal{IU}}_s}{{\\rm{outflow}}_{{\\rm{su}},h-\\tau_{{\\rm{su}},s},m,y}^{\\rm{total}}}`)"
" and the net inflow (also called incremental inflow) of the drainage area"
" controlled by this hydropower reservoir "
"(:math:`{{\\rm{INFLOW}}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{net}}`), which can be expressed "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:762
msgid ""
"{\\rm{inflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}={{\\rm{INFLOW}}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{net}}+\\sum_{{\\rm{su}}\\in"
" "
"{\\mathcal{IU}}_s}{{\\rm{outflow}}_{{\\rm{su}},h-\\tau_{{\\rm{su}},s},m,y}^{\\rm{total}}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:767
msgid ""
"Note that PREP-SHOT assumes a constant water travel (or propagation) time"
" (:math:`{\\tau}_{{\\rm{su}},s}`). The total outflow of each reservoir "
"consists of three parts: upstream water withdrawal (i.e., water used for "
"non-hydro purposes such as agriculture irrigation and urban water supply)"
" (:math:`{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{withdraw}}`), generation flow "
"(i.e., water flow through the turbines of the hydropower plant) "
"(:math:`{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{gen}}`) and spillage flow (i.e., "
"water spilled over the spillways)  "
"(:math:`{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{spillage}}`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:769
msgid ""
"{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{total}}={\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{withdraw}}+{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{gen}}+{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{spillage}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:775
msgid "Reservoir outflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:777
msgid ""
"The generation flow and spillage flow of the reservoir are limited by the"
" maximum outflow capacity of turbines "
"(:math:`{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}_s^{\\rm{gen}}`) and spillway "
"(:math:`{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}_s^{\\rm{spillage}}`), respectively. The sum of "
"these two parts also needs to meet the minimum outflow required "
"(:math:`{{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}}_s`) for other purposes (e.g., ecological flow, "
"shipping flow). These constraints are summarized as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:779
msgid ""
"{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{gen}}&\\le{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}_s^{\\rm{gen}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{spillage}}&\\le{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}_s^{\\rm{spillage}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y\\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"{{\\rm{OUTFLOW}}}_s & \\le "
"{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{gen}}+{\\rm{outflow}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{spillage}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:789
msgid "Reservoir storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:791
msgid ""
"The initial (when :math:`h=h_{\\rm{start}}`) and terminal (when "
":math:`h=h_{\\rm{end}}`) storage "
"(:math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h=h_{\\rm{start}},m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}` and "
":math:`{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h=h_{\\rm{end}},m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}`) of "
"hydropower reservoir in each month of each year should be assigned as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:793
msgid ""
"{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h=h_{\\rm{start}},m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}={{\\rm{STORAGE}}}_{s,m,y}^{\\rm{initreservoir}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,m,y \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h=h_{\\rm{end}},m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}={{\\rm{STORAGE}}}_{s,m,y}^{\\rm{endreservoir}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,m,y\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:800
msgid ""
"The reservoir storage is bounded between the maximum "
"(:math:`{\\overline{{\\rm{STORAGE}}}}_s^{\\rm{reservoir}}`) and minimum "
"storage (:math:`{\\underline{{\\rm{STORAGE}}}}_s^{\\rm{reservoir}}`) "
"depending on the functions (e.g., flood control, recreation, and water "
"supply) of the reservoir:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Mathematical_notations.rst:802
msgid ""
"{\\underline{{\\rm{STORAGE}}}}_s^{\\rm{reservoir}}\\le "
"{\\rm{storage}}_{s,h,m,y}^{\\rm{reservoir}}\\le{\\overline{{\\rm{STORAGE}}}}_s^{\\rm{reservoir}}\\quad\\forall"
" s,h,m,y\n"
"\\\\"
msgstr ""

